ANNOUNCEMENT AND CALL FOR PAPERS _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _
TWENTY-SECOND ANNUAL SOFTWARE ENGINEERING WORKSHOP
December 3 - 4 , 1997
Goddard Space Flight Center Building 8 Auditorium Greenbelt , Maryland 20771 USA
PURPOSE
The Software Engineering Workshop is sponsored by the NASA / Goddard Space Flight Center ( GSFC ) Software Engineering Laboratory ( SEL ) , in conjunction with the University of Maryland ( U of MD ) and Computer Sciences Corporation ( CSC ) .
Software practitioners from around the world attend this forum to share experiences and exchange ideas and measured results in the use and evaluation of software methods , models , and tools .
The Twenty- Second Annual Software Engineering Workshop will be held Wednesday and Thursday , December 3 and 4 , 1997 , at GSFC in the Building 8 auditorium .
The SEL invites you to take an active part in this meeting .
CALL FOR PAPERS
We are soliciting papers to be presented and discussed at this workshop . Topics of major interest include :
* Experiments in Software Development or Management * Experiences with Software Models , Technologies , and Environments * Software Measures * Product and Process Improvement * Component- Based Software Development ( processes that support COTS )
1997 SCHEDULE
* September 15 - Deadline for receipt of abstracts * October 10 - Notification to authors * October 24 - Issue final program * November 17 - Deadline for receipt of electronic file containing final slides ( if slides are to be projected electronically ) * November 21 - Deadline for registration * November 24 - Deadline for receipt of final copies ( camera ready hardcopy or electronic file ) of all papers and slides * December 3 - 4 - Workshop
WORKSHOP FORMAT
The workshop will feature several paper sessions and a panel presentation on a current topic in software engineering . All sessions will provide ample opportunity for questions and discussion .
An evening social at the Goddard Employees' Recreation Center will cap Wednesday 's program .
SUBMISSION OF ABSTRACTS
If you are interested in presenting material at the Software Engineering Workshop , forward an abstract to the SEL before Monday , September 15 , 1997 . Submit the following :
* Detailed abstract ( 3 - 5 pages ) that clearly includes your results with the supporting data that you wish to present * Name of speaker and co-author ( s ) , voice phone number ( s ) , fax number ( s ) and e-mail address ( es ) ; AUTHORS need to acknowledge in advance if their co-authors plan to attend the workshop . Authors and co-authors who are foreign nationals may not be permitted to attend the workshop because of NASA GSFC security regulations . [ 1 ] See Restrictions on presenters and attendees from designated countries . * Speaker 's registration form and fee
Direct abstracts to :
Scott Green NASA / Goddard Space Flight Center Code 551 Greenbelt , MD 20771 USA FAX : ( 301 ) 286 - 0245 telephone : ( 301 ) 286 - 5076 [ 2 ] scott . e . green @ gsfc . nasa . gov
You will be notified promptly via electronic mail of the SEL 's receipt of your abstract . If you DO NOT receive notification within one week after submitting , please inquire . This concerns receipt of abstracts only .
You will be notified by October 10 , 1997 , as to the submission 's acceptance or rejection . Please do not inquire before then .
Please include your e-mail address , voice and fax numbers with your submission
LOCATION
Goddard Space Flight Center is in Greenbelt , Maryland , just outside of Washington , DC . It is near the Baltimore- Washington Parkway and the 95 / 495 expressway and beltway . Three airports serve this area : Baltimore - Washington International ( BWI ) , Washington National , and Dulles International . ( BWI is the most conveniently located to GSFC . )
